  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">I formulate several statements demonstrating that the local metric redefinition can be used to reduce the UV divergences present in the quantum action for the Einstein gravity in <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math> dimensions. In its most general form, the proposal is that any UV divergences in the quantum action can be removed by an appropriate field re-definition and a renormalization of cosmological constant.</subfield>
